    "statement": "Consider the series \\[ S=\\sum_{k=1}^{\\infty}\\operatorname{cot}^{-1}\\!\\left(\\frac{k^{2}+k+4}{2}\\right), \\] whose terms are $\\cot^{-1}3,\\ \\cot^{-1}5,\\ \\cot^{-1}8,\\ \\cot^{-1}12,\\dots$ (the arguments $(k^2+k+4)/2$ are integers because $k^2+k$ is always even). (a) Do not quote a ready-made telescoping rule. Prove from scratch that there is a constant $c>0$ for which \\[ \\operatorname{cot}^{-1}\\!\\left(\\frac{k^{2}+k+4}{2}\\right)=\\tan^{-1}\\!\\frac{k+1}{c}-\\tan^{-1}\\!\\frac{k}{c}\\qquad(k\\ge 1), \\] by exhibiting $c$ explicitly and justifying that no $\\pm\\pi$ correction is needed. (b) Hence evaluate $S$ in closed form.",
