          "Justify the absence of a $\\pm\\pi$ correction. For $k\\ge1$ both $\\tan^{-1}\\frac{k+1}{2}$ and $\\tan^{-1}\\frac{k}{2}$ lie in $(0,\\tfrac{\\pi}{2})$, so their difference lies in $(-\\tfrac{\\pi}{2},\\tfrac{\\pi}{2})$, which is exactly the principal range of $\\tan^{-1}$. Equivalently the product $\\frac{k+1}{2}\\cdot\\frac{k}{2}>0$ keeps the subtraction formula on its principal branch. Hence $\\tan^{-1}\\frac{2}{k^2+k+4}=\\tan^{-1}\\frac{k+1}{2}-\\tan^{-1}\\frac{k}{2}$ with no adjustment.",
          "Telescope: $\\displaystyle\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\Big(\\tan^{-1}\\tfrac{k+1}{2}-\\tan^{-1}\\tfrac{k}{2}\\Big)=\\tan^{-1}\\tfrac{n+1}{2}-\\tan^{-1}\\tfrac12.$ Let $n\\to\\infty$: $\\tan^{-1}\\frac{n+1}{2}\\to\\frac{\\pi}{2}$, so $S=\\frac{\\pi}{2}-\\tan^{-1}\\frac12=\\boxed{\\tan^{-1}2}$ (using $\\tan^{-1}t+\\tan^{-1}\\frac1t=\\frac{\\pi}{2}$ for $t>0$)."
