          "Telescope from this end: $\\displaystyle\\sum_{k=1}^{n}\\Big(\\cot^{-1}\\tfrac{k}{2}-\\cot^{-1}\\tfrac{k+1}{2}\\Big)=\\cot^{-1}\\tfrac12-\\cot^{-1}\\tfrac{n+1}{2}.$",
          "As $n\\to\\infty$, $\\cot^{-1}\\frac{n+1}{2}\\to0$, leaving $S=\\cot^{-1}\\frac12$. Since $\\cot^{-1}\\frac12=\\tan^{-1}2$, we get $S=\\boxed{\\tan^{-1}2}$. Note the first survivor is $\\cot^{-1}\\frac12=\\tan^{-1}2$, not $\\cot^{-1}1=\\frac{\\pi}{4}$ — the anchor $\\frac12$ is the entire content of the answer."
