          "Part (b). The integrand $e^{\\Phi(x)}\\tfrac{1}{1+x^2}$ has a jump discontinuity at $x=0$, so the integral must be split there: $I=\\displaystyle\\int_{-1}^{0}e^{-\\pi/2}\\frac{dx}{1+x^2}+\\int_{0}^{1}e^{\\pi/2}\\frac{dx}{1+x^2}$, using $\\Phi=-\\tfrac{\\pi}{2}$ on $(-1,0)$ and $\\Phi=+\\tfrac{\\pi}{2}$ on $(0,1)$ from part (a).",
