          "Pin each constant by a sample. At $x=0$ (in $x>-1$): $S(0)=\\tan^{-1}0-\\tan^{-1}(-1)=0+\\tfrac{\\pi}{4}=\\tfrac{\\pi}{4}$. At $x=-2$ (in $x<-1$): $S(-2)=\\tan^{-1}(-2)-\\tan^{-1}\\frac{-3}{-1}=\\tan^{-1}(-2)-\\tan^{-1}3$; since $\\tan^{-1}2+\\tan^{-1}3=\\tfrac{3\\pi}{4}$, this is $-(\\tan^{-1}2+\\tan^{-1}3)=-\\tfrac{3\\pi}{4}$. Thus $F=\\tfrac{\\pi}{4}+\\tan^{-1}(x^{2})$ for $x>-1$ and $F=-\\tfrac{3\\pi}{4}+\\tan^{-1}(x^{2})$ for $x<-1$, proving (a).",
