    "statement": "For parameters $a,b>0$ define \\[ F(a,b)\\;=\\;\\sin^{-1}\\!\\frac{a}{\\sqrt{1+a^{2}}}\\;+\\;\\sin^{-1}\\!\\frac{b}{\\sqrt{1+b^{2}}}, \\] with principal branches $\\sin^{-1}t\\in\\left[-\\tfrac{\\pi}{2},\\tfrac{\\pi}{2}\\right]$ and $\\tan^{-1}t\\in\\left(-\\tfrac{\\pi}{2},\\tfrac{\\pi}{2}\\right)$. Prove that on the region $ab<1$ the expression collapses to the single closed form $F(a,b)=\\tan^{-1}\\!\\dfrac{a+b}{1-ab}$, and then determine the COMPLETE closed form of $F(a,b)$ for all $a,b>0$, identifying exactly the curve in the $(a,b)$-plane across which the formula must be corrected and by how much. A student rewrites each term as an arctangent, applies the addition formula, and submits $\\tan^{-1}\\dfrac{a+b}{1-ab}$ as the answer for every $a,b>0$. Show why this is right on one side of a curve, wrong by a fixed amount on the other side, and what the value is on the curve itself.",
