          "Hence $f\\ge\\tfrac{\\pi}{2}$ with equality only at $x=0$, and the supremum $\\tfrac{5\\pi}{4}$ is hit at $x=1$; continuity fills the gap, giving range $\\boxed{[\\tfrac{\\pi}{2},\\tfrac{5\\pi}{4}]}$. The decomposition makes the trap quantitative: the student silently replaced the even bump $2\\lvert\\tan^{-1}x\\rvert$ by $2\\tan^{-1}x$, which only matches on $x\\ge0$ and fabricates the spurious minimum $-\\tfrac{\\pi}{4}$ at $x=-1$."
