          "Read the argument. Real and imaginary parts are equal in magnitude ($|{-2-2\\sqrt2}|=2+2\\sqrt2$), so the reference angle to the axes is $\\tfrac{\\pi}{4}$; in QII the argument is $\\pi-\\tfrac{\\pi}{4}=\\tfrac{3\\pi}{4}$. Hence $\\Phi=\\boxed{\\dfrac{3\\pi}{4}}$. The negative real part announces the obtuse angle at a glance — the $-\\tfrac{\\pi}{4}$ from the bare formula would have demanded a point in QIV, which $(1+ix)^{2}$ is decidedly not."
