          "Set $s=\\sec^{-1}a$ and $c=\\csc^{-1}a$. The cofunction identity gives one equation for free: $s+c=\\tfrac{\\pi}{2}$ for every $|a|\\ge1$. The problem supplies the second: $c-s=\\tfrac{\\pi}{6}$.",
