          "Solve $\\tfrac1a=\\sin\\tfrac{\\pi}{3}=\\tfrac{\\sqrt3}{2}$ to get $\\boxed{a=\\tfrac{2}{\\sqrt3}}$. Since $\\csc^{-1}$ is strictly monotone on its branch, this is the only solution; the negative branch ($a\\le-1$) gives $\\csc^{-1}a<0$, which can never equal $+\\tfrac{\\pi}{3}$, so it contributes nothing."
