    "statement": "Consider the doubly nested function \\[F(x)=\\sin^{-1}\\!\\bigl(\\cos^{-1}x\\bigr)+\\cos^{-1}\\!\\bigl(\\sin^{-1}x\\bigr).\\] A student writes: \\[\\text{\"Every inverse-trig output and input lives in }[-1,1]\\text{, and both }\\sin^{-1}x,\\cos^{-1}x\\text{ need }x\\in[-1,1];\\ \\text{so the domain of }F\\text{ is }[-1,1].\\text{\"}\\] Determine the exact natural domain of $F$ (the set of all real $x$ at which $F$ is defined), expressed using exact constants. State whether the interval is symmetric about $0$, and identify both endpoints precisely.",
