          "Hence $\\operatorname{dom}F=[\\cos1,\\ \\sin1]$. The width is $\\sin1-\\cos1=\\sqrt2\\,\\sin\\!\\bigl(1-\\tfrac\\pi4\\bigr)\\approx0.301$, a thin asymmetric slab sitting entirely to the right of $0$ — so $x=0$ (which the student's $[-1,1]$ admits) is in fact excluded because $0<\\cos1$. $\\boxed{[\\cos1,\\ \\sin1]}$."
