          "Thus one period is a flat-topped zigzag: rise $0\\to\\pi$, plateau at $\\pi$, fall $\\pi\\to0$, plateau at $0$. The slope sequence $(+2,0,-2,0)$ changes value at each junction $x=\\tfrac{\\pi}{2},\\pi,\\tfrac{3\\pi}{2},2\\pi$, so within one open period $(0,2\\pi)$ the slope jumps at the three interior junctions $x=\\tfrac{\\pi}{2},\\pi,\\tfrac{3\\pi}{2}$, plus a corner at $x=0$ where a $+2$ arm meets a $0$ arm from the previous period.",
          "Since $h$ has period $2\\pi$, the corner pattern repeats. The interior breakpoints of $(-2\\pi,2\\pi)$ are $x=-\\tfrac{3\\pi}{2},-\\pi,-\\tfrac{\\pi}{2},0,\\tfrac{\\pi}{2},\\pi,\\tfrac{3\\pi}{2}$, and the slope is different on the two sides of each (one of $\\{+2,0,-2\\}$ meeting another). All seven are genuine corners, giving $\\boxed{7}$."
