    "statement": "All four arctangents below take their principal value in $\\left(-\\tfrac{\\pi}{2},\\tfrac{\\pi}{2}\\right)$. Evaluate exactly \\[ S=\\arctan 3+\\arctan 5+\\arctan 7+\\arctan 8. \\] Here is the cautionary tale of an over-eager apprentice. He chains the tangent-addition formula four deep, each time feeding the running tangent back in, and after the dust settles he reads $\\tan S=-1$. He then writes $S=\\arctan(-1)=-\\tfrac{\\pi}{4}$ and boxes it. Every one of $3,5,7,8$ exceeds $1$, so each arctangent already overshoots $\\tfrac{\\pi}{4}$; the running sum vaults across $\\tfrac{\\pi}{2}$, then $\\pi$, then $\\tfrac{3\\pi}{2}$ as the terms pile up. The addition formula, blind to every one of those crossings, reports only the destination modulo $\\pi$. Find the true value of $S$, and account for exactly how many hidden $+\\pi$ shifts separate the apprentice's principal answer from the truth.",
